enumerations.name: ChapterEnumBreak
enumerations.note: This allows to specify the page break policy of a paginatable element. Aggregated by Paginateable.break

literals.name: break
literals.description:
This indicates the a page break shall be applied before the current block.
Tags: atp.EnumerationLiteralIndex=0

literals.name: noBreak
literals.description:
This indicates that there is no need to force a page break before this block.
Tags: atp.EnumerationLiteralIndex=1

enumerations.name: KeepWithPreviousEnum
enumerations.note: This enumerator specifies a page break policy by controlling blocks which shall be kept together. Aggregated by Paginateable.keepWithPrevious

literals.name: keep
literals.description:
This indicates that the block shall be kept together with the previous block.
Tags: atp.EnumerationLiteralIndex=0

literals.name: noKeep
literals.description:
This indicates that there is no need to keep the block with the previous one. This is the same as if the attribute itself is missing.
Tags: atp.EnumerationLiteralIndex=1
